comments: LLB and LLS show Young (ATL) makes slight contact to Dinwiddie's (BKN) arm at the end of the drive but the contact does not affect Dinwiddie's ability to make his intended pass.
RLS shows Young (ATL) makes contact to the body of Russell (BKN) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Len (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Harris (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RLS shows Allen (BKN) makes incidental contact to the arm of Huerter (ATL) after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
LLS and RLS show Carroll (BKN) holds the arm of Len (ATL) affecting his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
LLB shows Huerter (ATL) wraps Carroll (BKN) and affects his SQBR.
Collins (ATL) firms up in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and absorbs the contact.
RLS and RLB show Dinwiddie (BKN) makes contact to Young's (ATL) body on the drive that affects his SQBR.
Collins (ATL) and Carroll (BKN) engage and separate during the rebound.

RLS and RLB show Huerter (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Dinwiddie (BKN). There is no conclusive angle that shows if Huerter makes contact with Dinwiddie's arm during the drive.
RLB shows Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Allen (BKN) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the play at the basket by Collins (ATL).
As Len (ATL) attempts to get through the legal screen set by Harris (BKN), he delivers contact to Allen (BKN) that affects his FOM.
Harris (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Prince (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Huerter (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact during the driving shot attempt by Russell (BKN).
Allen (BKN) and Len (ATL) engage and separate during the rebound.
Allen (BKN) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Young (ATL) before both players briefly engage with their arms before separating.
LLB shows Young (ATL) absorbs contact during the driving shot attempt by Dinwiddie (BKN) and makes legal contact to Dinwiddie's hand that is on the ball.

Young (ATL) makes incidental foot to foot contact with his teammate Collins (ATL) and the contact causes him to fall to the floor.  The crew determines the whistle was inadvertent and awards Atlanta the ball out of bounds.
LAR shows Prince (ATL) kicks his leg out unnaturally on the jump shot attempt to create contact with Russell (BKN) but it does not affect Russell's ability to defend.
Harris (BKN) and Allen (BKN) make clean contact with the ball during the rebound and a jump ball is correctly called between Allen and Collins (ATL).
Young (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position on Dinwiddie (BKN) during the drive and the contact is marginal.
Collins (ATL) commits a take foul on Harris (BKN).
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dinwiddie (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position on Young (ATL) during the drive.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (BKN) and does not deliver contact.
Harris (BKN) does not impede Collins (ATL) during the potential rebound as the clock expires.
